What is Cloud Computing?
•	It is the use of remote servers on the internet to store, manage and process data rather than a local server or personal computer.

Application+platform+infrastructure – cloud computing

Cloud models:
•	IAAS – Infrastructure as a service (only infrastructure without os) – System admins
•	PAAS – Platform as a service (with os) - Developers
•	SAAS – Software as a service – End user
Types of cloud:
•	Public cloud
•	Private cloud
•	Hybrid cloud

Hybrid cloud act as a bridge between public and private cloud to communicate.

Benefits of Cloud Based Computing
1. No upfront expenses for creating servers
2. No expense for maintaining servers
3. Benefit from massive economies of scale
4. Increase speed and agility
5. Go global in minutes
